注意，抢劫攻击被害人…

33
00:03:38,585 --> 00:03:40,519
Four-eight, this is Romano. Robbery and assault victim...

34
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:42,545
脸部受伤，在东42街入口

35
00:03:40,587 --> 00:03:42,578
with facial wound at East 42nd entrance.

36
00:03:42,622 --> 00:03:44,749
先生，请你站过来

37
00:03:42,655 --> 00:03:44,782
Sir, I'd like you to just stand right there.

38
00:03:45,191 --> 00:03:46,385
好

39
00:03:44,857 --> 00:03:48,020
- Certainly. - Are you traveling somewhere?

40
00:03:46,759 --> 00:03:47,987
你要去哪儿？

41
00:03:48,094 --> 00:03:51,427
I have arrived. My travels are over for the time being.

42
00:03:48,361 --> 00:03:51,387
我刚到，暂时不会走

43
00:03:51,798 --> 00:03:53,060
你的行李呢？

44
00:03:51,497 --> 00:03:52,930
Where's your luggage?

45
00:03:54,367 --> 00:03:56,130
我没有行李

46
00:03:54,167 --> 00:03:57,967
- I don't require luggage. - Do you have a ticket?

47
00:03:56,202 --> 00:03:57,965
你的车票呢？

48
00:03:58,037 --> 00:03:59,937
火车票？票根呢？

49
00:03:58,037 --> 00:03:59,971
<i>Train ticket? Ticket stub?</i>

50
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:02,564
我不是坐火车来的

51
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:02,598
I didn't arrive by train.

52
00:04:02,675 --> 00:04:04,540
麻烦你把太阳眼镜拿掉

53
00:04:02,675 --> 00:04:04,540
Would you remove your sunglasses for me, please?

54
00:04:05,645 --> 00:04:06,907
最好不要

55
00:04:05,612 --> 00:04:10,345
Oh, I'd rather not. I'd forgotten, but I mean, wow,

56
00:04:07,547 --> 00:04:10,345
我完全忘了…

57
00:04:10,450 --> 00:04:12,475
你们的星球有多亮

58
00:04:10,416 --> 00:04:12,509
your planet is really bright.

59
00:04:13,119 --> 00:04:15,952
是吗？东42街 有名男子精神异常

60
00:04:12,585 --> 00:04:15,986
I see. East 42, we have an E.D.P.

61
00:04:16,055 --> 00:04:18,080
麻烦你跟我们回去

62
00:04:16,055 --> 00:04:18,114
I have to ask you to come with us, sir.

63
00:04:18,191 --> 00:04:20,091
没问题

64
00:04:18,191 --> 00:04:20,125
<i>- Of course. - [Handcuffs Lock]</i>

65
00:04:41,714 --> 00:04:43,705
费迪

66
00:04:41,581 --> 00:04:42,912
<i>[Female Officer] Freddy!</i>

67
00:04:44,951 --> 00:04:47,613
他是不是从月台出来的？

68
00:04:44,951 --> 00:04:46,976
Did you see this fella come out of a gate?

69
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:50,951
不是，他突然就出现了

70
00:04:47,387 --> 00:04:50,982
He didn't come from no gate. Brother came from nowhere.

71
00:04:51,557 --> 00:04:53,047
你明白我的意思吗？

72
00:04:51,057 --> 00:04:53,116
<i>You know what I'm saying?</i>

73
00:04:53,159 --> 00:04:55,184
明白，我明白你的意思

74
00:04:53,192 --> 00:04:55,217
Yeah, Freddy, I know what you're saying.

75
00:05:00,867 --> 00:05:02,801
<i>[Car Door Closes]</i>

76
00:05:04,737 --> 00:05:08,673
<i>[Car Engine Starts]</i>

77
00:06:31,457 --> 00:06:34,324
“曼哈顿精神疗养院”

78
00:06:40,933 --> 00:06:43,663
<i>[Car Door Opens, Closes]</i>

79
00:06:43,603 --> 00:06:45,400
我不要出去

80
00:06:43,736 --> 00:06:47,502
<i>I don't wanna go outside, because there's things that can kill you...</i>

81
00:06:45,505 --> 00:06:47,803
外面太危险了

82
00:06:52,745 --> 00:06:54,679
谢谢

83
00:06:52,745 --> 00:06:53,837
thank you.

84
00:06:54,781 --> 00:06:56,772
你要是闻到那些化学物质

85
00:06:54,747 --> 00:06:56,806
If you breathe all those chemicals out there,

86
00:06:56,883 --> 00:06:59,443
尤其是宇宙辐射线 和西尼罗河病毒

87
00:06:56,883 --> 00:06:59,647
not to mention the cosmic rays and the West Nile virus,

88
00:06:59,552 --> 00:07:00,985
还有那个…

89
00:06:59,719 --> 00:07:03,519
and that other one... the new airborne pigeon disease nobody wants to talk about.

90
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:03,487
没人敢提的新鸽子传染病

91
00:07:03,589 --> 00:07:05,454
我听过那个病

92
00:07:03,589 --> 00:07:05,489
The new pigeon disease. I've heard of that.

93
00:07:05,558 --> 00:07:08,391
我最受不了的是伙食

94
00:07:05,558 --> 00:07:08,459
Another thing that's been bothering me is the food.

95
00:07:08,494 --> 00:07:11,520
餐厅的食物不够热，有细菌

96
00:07:08,528 --> 00:07:11,554
The cafeteria serves lukewarm food, full of germs.

97
00:07:11,631 --> 00:07:13,758
鲍威尔医生，你们应该想想办法

98
00:07:11,631 --> 00:07:13,496
<i>You really need to do something about that, Dr. Powell.</i>

99
00:07:13,866 --> 00:07:15,925
加热才能杀菌

100
00:07:13,533 --> 00:07:15,797
Heat is the only thing that kills germs. Heat.

101
00:07:16,035 --> 00:07:19,562
知道了，我们会注意

102
00:07:15,868 --> 00:07:19,599
<i>Point taken. We'll look into that right away.</i>

103
00:07:19,672 --> 00:07:21,606
另外呢…

104
00:07:19,672 --> 00:07:24,109
In the meantime, I want you to start taking your medication again.

105
00:07:21,707 --> 00:07:24,073
我要你开始吃药

106
00:07:24,177 --> 00:07:26,839
帮助你入睡，你要好好睡觉

107
00:07:24,177 --> 00:07:26,873
It'll help you sleep. And you need the sleep, Ernie.

108
00:07:27,413 --> 00:07:28,880
对你的身体好

109
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:28,914
Sleep is good.

110
00:07:28,981 --> 00:07:31,006
<i>[Buzzer Buzzes]</i>

111
00:07:32,185 --> 00:07:34,779
时间到了吗？

112
00:07:32,251 --> 00:07:33,479
Is our time up?

113
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:37,214
今天的时间到了

114
00:07:34,887 --> 00:07:37,253
Only for today, Ernie.

115
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:42,059
两通电话，你太太叫你带瓶酒

116
00:07:39,592 --> 00:07:42,083
Two calls: Your wife, bring home a bottle of wine.

117
00:07:42,161 --> 00:07:44,061
好         还有查克伯堤医生

118
00:07:42,161 --> 00:07:44,095
- Yeah. - And Dr. Chakraborty.

119
00:07:44,197 --> 00:07:46,665
他要你看一下转院病人的资料

120
00:07:44,163 --> 00:07:46,688
A transfer from Bellevue he wants you to take a look at.

121
00:07:46,766 --> 00:07:51,203
好极了，这次是谁 耶稣还是圣女贞德

122
00:07:46,766 --> 00:07:51,226
Great. Who is it this time? Jesus Christ or Joan of Arc?

123
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:53,966
查克伯堤医生没说

124
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:53,363
Dr. Chakraborty didn't say.

125
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,631
他一个月前入院

126
00:08:20,533 --> 00:08:22,660
<i>[Man] He arrived at Bellevue a month ago,</i>

127
00:08:22,735 --> 00:08:25,169
起先怀疑他服食迷幻药

128
00:08:22,735 --> 00:08:25,203
<i>suspicion of hallucinogenic intoxication.</i>

129
00:08:25,271 --> 00:08:28,502
可是又验不出任何药物反应

130
00:08:25,271 --> 00:08:28,536
<i>But, uh, he was found negative for substances of any kind.</i>

131
00:08:28,608 --> 00:08:30,906
心电图和血液都很正常

132
00:08:28,608 --> 00:08:30,906
His EKG, his blood value are all normal.

133
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:33,035
没有脑震荡，没有脑肿瘤

134
00:08:30,977 --> 00:08:33,309
There's no sign of concussion, no brain tumor,

135
00:08:33,145 --> 00:08:34,772
没有颞叶癫痫

136
00:08:33,379 --> 00:08:37,145
no temporal lobe, epilepsy, no indication of organic abnormality whatsoever.

137
00:08:34,881 --> 00:08:37,111
也没有任何器官异常的迹象

138
00:08:37,450 --> 00:08:39,611
不过，治疗一个月以后

139
00:08:37,216 --> 00:08:39,684
However, after one month,

140
00:08:39,719 --> 00:08:42,552
他的健忘症、妄想症还是存在

141
00:08:39,752 --> 00:08:42,585
his amnesia and his delusion have persisted.

142
00:08:43,723 --> 00:08:46,089
他自称不是人类

143
00:08:43,756 --> 00:08:46,122
He claims to be not human.

144
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:47,489
是外星人

145
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:48,660
A visitor from another planet.

146
00:08:48,694 --> 00:08:51,663
注射了三个礼拜的镇定剂

147
00:08:48,728 --> 00:08:51,526
They administered thorazine on this guy for three weeks...

148
00:08:51,764 --> 00:08:55,291
每天三百毫克，他都没反应

149
00:08:51,597 --> 00:08:55,328
at 300 milligrams a day, and he was unresponsive?

150
00:08:55,401 --> 00:08:58,928
注射三百毫克也没反应？ 不可能

151
00:08:55,401 --> 00:08:58,837
How can you be unresponsive to 300 milligrams of thorazine? It's impossible.

152
00:08:59,005 --> 00:09:00,768
所以才交给你

153
00:08:58,905 --> 00:09:00,930
That's why they sent him to you.

154
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:03,465
太好了

155
00:09:01,007 --> 00:09:03,168
[Sighs] Terrific.

156
00:09:03,576 --> 00:09:06,909
没有身份证 没有失踪人口报告

157
00:09:03,576 --> 00:09:06,943
No I.D., no missing persons report matching his description.

158
00:09:07,013 --> 00:09:09,379
这是什么？

159
00:09:07,013 --> 00:09:08,241
What's this?

160
00:09:09,482 --> 00:09:11,109
在他身上找到的

161
00:09:08,981 --> 00:09:10,175
<i>He had it on him.</i>

162
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:18,012
希望外星人可以申请医疗补助

163
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:18,081
Well, let's hope extraterrestrials qualify for Medicaid.

164
00:09:19,659 --> 00:09:21,422
医生，他来了

165
00:09:19,659 --> 00:09:20,648
[Secretary] He's here, Doctor.

166
00:09:21,527 --> 00:09:24,121
谢谢你，乔伊斯

167
00:09:21,193 --> 00:09:22,660
Thank you, Joyce.

168
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:29,634
医疗记录287号，自称帕特

169
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:28,963
Medical record 2-8-7. Calls himself Prot.

170
00:09:29,035 --> 00:09:31,094
<i>[Knock At Door, Door Opens]</i>

171
00:09:32,805 --> 00:09:34,966
医生，这家伙像猫一样温驯

172
00:09:32,638 --> 00:09:35,004
This one's as gentle as a pussycat, Doc.

173
00:09:35,074 --> 00:09:37,634
进来，请坐

174
00:09:35,741 --> 00:09:37,140
Come in. Have a seat.

175
00:09:38,210 --> 00:09:41,805
请坐？奇怪的说法

176
00:09:38,210 --> 00:09:41,839
"Have a seat." Curious expression.

177
00:09:43,683 --> 00:09:46,117
让我自我介绍一下…

178
00:09:43,683 --> 00:09:46,151
Well, let me introduce myself. I'm...

179
00:09:46,218 --> 00:09:48,778
马克鲍威尔医生 临床精神科主治医师

180
00:09:46,218 --> 00:09:48,812
Dr. Mark Powell, Chief of Clinical Psychiatry...

181
00:09:48,888 --> 00:09:51,356
在曼哈顿精神疗养院服务

182
00:09:48,888 --> 00:09:51,379
of the Manhattan Psychiatric Institute.

183
00:09:51,724 --> 00:09:54,249
很好，你知道自己在哪儿

184
00:09:51,457 --> 00:09:53,948
Good. You know where you are.

185
00:09:55,728 --> 00:09:58,663
那么…

186
00:09:55,728 --> 00:09:59,755
Well, now, uh... Prot, is it?

187
00:09:58,764 --> 00:10:01,358
你叫帕特？         波特

188
00:09:59,832 --> 00:10:03,131
- "Prote." - I see, "Prote."

189
00:10:01,834 --> 00:10:03,096
好，波特

190
00:10:03,202 --> 00:10:06,171
<i>- Well, Prot, we're here to... - May I?</i>

191
00:10:03,502 --> 00:10:06,096
波特，我们要… 可以吗？

192
00:10:07,506 --> 00:10:08,598
请便

193
00:10:07,540 --> 00:10:08,632
Please.

194
00:10:12,612 --> 00:10:15,274
你们叫这个苹果品种红蛇果

195
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:15,304
Red delicious. You call this variety.

196
00:10:16,482 --> 00:10:18,814
是我最喜欢吃的

197
00:10:16,415 --> 00:10:18,349
It's my favorite.

198
00:10:18,918 --> 00:10:22,217
我想先问你知不知道…

199
00:10:18,918 --> 00:10:21,409
<i>I'd like to begin by asking you...</i>

200
00:10:22,655 --> 00:10:24,885
自己为什么在这里

201
00:10:22,321 --> 00:10:24,551
if you know why you're here.

202
00:10:25,358 --> 00:10:28,259
当然，你们以为我疯了

203
00:10:24,957 --> 00:10:27,755
Of course. You think I'm crazy.

204
00:10:30,429 --> 00:10:32,659
我们用“病”这个字

205
00:10:30,429 --> 00:10:35,025
We prefer the term "ill." Do you think you are ill?

206
00:10:32,765 --> 00:10:35,097
你认为自己有病吗？

207
00:10:35,167 --> 00:10:36,395
也许吧，有点想家

208
00:10:35,101 --> 00:10:36,398
A little homesick, perhaps.

209
00:10:36,802 --> 00:10:40,067
真的？你家在哪儿？

210
00:10:36,802 --> 00:10:40,101
Really. Where is home?

211
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:42,371
K-PAX星

212
00:10:41,173 --> 00:10:42,197
K-PAX.

213
00:10:42,608 --> 00:10:43,768
K-PAX星？

214
00:10:42,441 --> 00:10:43,533
K-PAX?

215
00:10:43,876 --> 00:10:46,743
大写K，连字号，大写PAX

216
00:10:43,776 --> 00:10:46,768
Capital "K," hyphen, capitals "P-A-X."

217
00:10:46,846 --> 00:10:49,440
K派斯是个星球

218
00:10:46,846 --> 00:10:48,780
K-PAX is a planet.

219
00:10:49,548 --> 00:10:52,847
放心，我不会寄生在你身上

220
00:10:49,348 --> 00:10:52,875
But don't worry, I'm not going to leap out of your chest.

221
00:10:53,953 --> 00:10:55,818
我并不担心

222
00:10:53,786 --> 00:10:55,185
I'm not worried.

223
00:10:55,921 --> 00:10:58,253
问题是，我只知道九大行星

224
00:10:55,921 --> 00:10:58,355
It's just that I'm only familiar with nine planets.

225
00:10:58,357 --> 00:11:00,985
其实是十大行星，不过没关系

226
00:10:58,424 --> 00:11:00,824
Well, actually, there are ten, but that doesn't matter.

227
00:11:01,093 --> 00:11:02,993
我不是来自这个太阳系

228
00:11:00,893 --> 00:11:03,020
I'm not from your solar system.

229
00:11:03,095 --> 00:11:06,428
K派斯距离地球一千光年

230
00:11:03,095 --> 00:11:06,428
K-PAX is about 1,000 of your light-years away from here...

231
00:11:06,532 --> 00:11:09,228
在你们所谓的天琴座附近

232
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:09,263
in what you would call your constellation Lyra.

233
00:11:09,335 --> 00:11:11,599
那么远

234
00:11:09,335 --> 00:11:10,768
That's quite a ways.

235
00:11:11,704 --> 00:11:13,672
你是怎么来地球的

236
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:13,730
I'm curious. How did you get to Earth?

237
00:11:17,209 --> 00:11:20,007
这是如何运用光能的问题

