How do you know to come? How does the boy call you?

1896
01:11:29,901 --> 01:11:33,894
我也不知道，我只知道我来了

1897
01:11:29,900 --> 01:11:33,961
I don't know. I just come. I just... I just know.

1898
01:11:34,472 --> 01:11:35,996
你怎么来地球的？

1899
01:11:34,037 --> 01:11:36,062
How do you get to Earth?

1900
01:11:36,408 --> 01:11:39,639
我想出去，可不可以出去？

1901
01:11:36,139 --> 01:11:39,666
I wanna go outside. Can I go outside?

1902
01:11:39,744 --> 01:11:41,644
马克，看他的身体语言

1903
01:11:39,743 --> 01:11:41,677
Uh, read... read his body language, Mark.

1904
01:11:41,746 --> 01:11:44,271
他不想再说下去了

1905
01:11:41,745 --> 01:11:44,305
L-I don't think he wants to talk anymore today.

1906
01:11:44,382 --> 01:11:46,282
好吧，波特

1907
01:11:44,381 --> 01:11:46,315
All right. Prot?

1908
01:11:46,384 --> 01:11:49,114
我要你放松

1909
01:11:46,383 --> 01:11:49,147
- I want you to just relax now. - [Shuddering]

1910
01:11:49,220 --> 01:11:51,745
想着星星

1911
01:11:49,219 --> 01:11:51,813
- Think about the stars. - [Whimpers]

1912
01:11:53,458 --> 01:11:57,554
对了，我要从五倒数到一

1913
01:11:53,490 --> 01:11:57,620
<i>That's right. I'm gonna count backwards now from five to one,</i>

1914
01:11:57,662 --> 01:12:01,063
你醒来的时候会非常有精神

1915
01:11:57,694 --> 01:12:01,095
and you'll find yourself wide-awake and refreshed.

1916
01:12:01,166 --> 01:12:04,761
五，你现在开始醒过来

1917
01:12:01,164 --> 01:12:04,827
Five. You're starting to come out of it now.

1918
01:12:04,869 --> 01:12:07,201
四，你越来越清醒

1919
01:12:04,901 --> 01:12:07,267
<i>Four. You're feeling more alert.</i>

1920
01:12:07,305 --> 01:12:09,466
三，变得更清醒

1921
01:12:07,337 --> 01:12:09,498
<i>Three. Even more alert.</i>

1922
01:12:09,574 --> 01:12:12,099
二，你醒过来了

1923
01:12:09,573 --> 01:12:12,201
<i>Two. You're becoming awake now.</i>

1924
01:12:12,210 --> 01:12:14,178
一

1925
01:12:12,275 --> 01:12:14,209
<i>And one.</i>

1926
01:12:18,817 --> 01:12:20,614
我们什么时候开始？

1927
01:12:18,715 --> 01:12:20,649
So when do we begin?

1928
01:12:20,985 --> 01:12:22,646
已经结束了

1929
01:12:20,717 --> 01:12:22,685
It's already over.

1930
01:12:26,491 --> 01:12:30,086
哦，迅雷不及掩耳

1931
01:12:26,523 --> 01:12:30,118
Oh, the old "fastest gun in the West" routine, huh?

1932
01:12:31,695 --> 01:12:33,890
<i>[Slaps Knee]</i>

1933
01:12:36,634 --> 01:12:41,594
找出全美国屠宰场的地址

1934
01:12:36,633 --> 01:12:41,593
Let's find the locations of all the slaughterhouses operating in the United States.

1935
01:12:41,706 --> 01:12:45,039
查查一共有多少家

1936
01:12:41,671 --> 01:12:45,038
I mean, how many can there be?

1937
01:12:45,143 --> 01:12:47,043
我不知道

1938
01:12:45,108 --> 01:12:47,042
I don't know.

1939
01:12:47,145 --> 01:12:50,808
不要找那些靠近大城市

1940
01:12:47,110 --> 01:12:50,807
We eliminate, uh, the ones in or near big cities...

1941
01:12:50,915 --> 01:12:55,318
只要找小镇、乡村地区

1942
01:12:50,881 --> 01:12:55,341
<i>and we concentrate on small towns, rural areas,</i>

1943
01:12:55,420 --> 01:12:59,550
可以看到星星的地方

1944
01:12:55,418 --> 01:12:59,582
you know, places where you can see the stars.

1945
01:13:01,159 --> 01:13:03,992
乔伊斯，我们只剩六天了

1946
01:13:01,157 --> 01:13:04,024
Joyce, we only have six days.

1947
01:13:07,499 --> 01:13:09,990
我要不要带水晶杯走？

1948
01:13:06,129 --> 01:13:07,562
<i>[Chattering]</i>

1949
01:13:07,631 --> 01:13:10,065
Shall I bring the crystal or leave it here?

1950
01:13:10,368 --> 01:13:13,064
在K派斯搞不好用不到

1951
01:13:10,133 --> 01:13:13,068
I suppose I won't really need it on K-PAX.

1952
01:13:13,171 --> 01:13:16,197
我连他们喝什么都不知道

1953
01:13:13,136 --> 01:13:16,196
I don't even know what they drink. [Laughing]

1954
01:13:16,307 --> 01:13:19,435
你在做梦 他只带一个人跟他走

1955
01:13:16,273 --> 01:13:19,436
Dream on, sister. He can only take one of us with him.

1956
01:13:19,544 --> 01:13:23,537
你一身臭味，干嘛要带你 要带也带我

1957
01:13:19,509 --> 01:13:22,569
Why the hell would he take a stinker like you? He's taking me.

1958
01:13:23,648 --> 01:13:26,082
乱说，我不臭

1959
01:13:22,646 --> 01:13:26,104
<i>How dare you! I do not stink.</i>

1960
01:13:26,184 --> 01:13:28,448
少做梦了，应该是我

1961
01:13:26,182 --> 01:13:28,514
Nah, forget it, ho. I'm the one goin'.

1962
01:13:28,553 --> 01:13:30,953
是哦，哪一个你？

1963
01:13:28,585 --> 01:13:30,917
Yeah? Which one of you?

1964
01:13:31,055 --> 01:13:34,650
好，谁要先发言

1965
01:13:30,987 --> 01:13:34,684
<i>Okay. Who would like to begin?</i>

1966
01:13:34,759 --> 01:13:38,126
恩尼         我在想

1967
01:13:34,758 --> 01:13:39,127
- Ernie. - Uh, l-I was... I was wondering if it was possible...

1968
01:13:38,229 --> 01:13:41,426
可不可以不吃麦皮，改吃麦片

1969
01:13:39,195 --> 01:13:41,459
- for us to have Cream of Wheat instead of oatmeal. - [All Groaning]

1970
01:13:41,533 --> 01:13:44,127
又来了         豪伊

1971
01:13:41,531 --> 01:13:44,193
- Not again. - Howie.

1972
01:13:44,235 --> 01:13:47,602
我有个提议，因为时间不多了

1973
01:13:44,267 --> 01:13:47,634
<i>I have a suggestion, because there's really, really not much time.</i>

1974
01:13:47,705 --> 01:13:50,799
我建议举办作文比赛

1975
01:13:47,704 --> 01:13:50,867
I would like to propose an essay contest...

1976
01:13:50,909 --> 01:13:54,572
来决定谁跟波特走

1977
01:13:50,941 --> 01:13:54,638
to decide once and for all who will go with Prot.

1978
01:13:54,679 --> 01:14:00,379
我跟他谈过 他答应在7月27日前看完

1979
01:13:54,711 --> 01:13:59,978
I've spoken with him, and he's agreed to read them all by July 27.

1980
01:14:00,485 --> 01:14:05,616
想去的人，请写清楚原因

1981
01:14:00,016 --> 01:14:02,382
<i>So if anyone would like to be considered,</i>

1982
01:14:02,452 --> 01:14:05,683
please state your reasons in a clear, legible hand...

1983
01:14:05,723 --> 01:14:08,886
然后交给我

1984
01:14:05,755 --> 01:14:08,918
- and return them to me. - [Excited Chattering]

1985
01:14:08,993 --> 01:14:10,585
罗素

1986
01:14:08,992 --> 01:14:10,084
Russell.

1987
01:14:12,162 --> 01:14:14,653
<i>- [Chattering Continues] - Yes?</i>

1988
01:14:13,665 --> 01:14:14,632
贝丝？

1989
01:14:16,868 --> 01:14:20,395
我可不可以带圣经去K派斯

1990
01:14:16,933 --> 01:14:20,460
<i>Would I get to take my bible to K-PAX?</i>

1991
01:14:21,372 --> 01:14:22,839
当然可以

1992
01:14:20,537 --> 01:14:22,903
Of course you would.

1993
01:14:22,941 --> 01:14:25,774
作文可以晚一点写

1994
01:14:22,973 --> 01:14:25,840
<i>[Betty] We can finish the essays later.</i>

1995
01:14:33,618 --> 01:14:36,212
现在，我要你再回到过去

1996
01:14:33,650 --> 01:14:36,278
<i>[Dr. Powell] Now, I want you to go back in time again,</i>

1997
01:14:36,321 --> 01:14:38,551
但是不要像上次那么久远

1998
01:14:36,353 --> 01:14:38,617
<i>but not so far back as last time.</i>

1999
01:14:41,526 --> 01:14:44,086
你朋友还在吗？

2000
01:14:41,124 --> 01:14:44,116
- [Chuckles] - Is your friend there?

2001
01:14:44,195 --> 01:14:47,255
跟你在一起

2002
01:14:44,194 --> 01:14:47,288
- Is he with you now? - [Chuckling]

2003
01:14:47,365 --> 01:14:49,993
对

2004
01:14:47,364 --> 01:14:48,695
Yeah.

2005
01:14:50,068 --> 01:14:51,057
他叫什么名字？

2006
01:14:50,266 --> 01:14:53,133
- What's his name? - I'm not tellin'.

2007
01:14:51,135 --> 01:14:52,625
我不告诉你

2008
01:14:54,272 --> 01:14:57,036
波特，我想知道你朋友叫什么

2009
01:14:54,337 --> 01:14:57,067
Prot, I would like to know your friend's name.

2010
01:14:57,141 --> 01:14:59,575
我就是不告诉你

2011
01:14:57,140 --> 01:14:59,608
Well, I ain't gonna tell ya.

2012
01:15:03,014 --> 01:15:06,177
那我们得帮他取个名字

2013
01:15:03,046 --> 01:15:06,209
Well, we have to call him something.

2014
01:15:06,284 --> 01:15:08,309
叫他皮特吧

2015
01:15:06,282 --> 01:15:08,341
- How about Pete? - [Chuckling]

2016
01:15:08,419 --> 01:15:12,116
他不叫皮特，不过随便你

2017
01:15:08,418 --> 01:15:11,649
Well, that's not his name, but whatever thrills you.

2018
01:15:12,657 --> 01:15:16,923
那是哪一年？      1985年

2019
01:15:12,722 --> 01:15:16,988
- What year is it? - It's 1985.

2020
01:15:17,028 --> 01:15:20,259
你几岁         175岁

2021
01:15:17,060 --> 01:15:20,325
- How old are you? - One hundred and seventy-five.

2022
01:15:20,698 --> 01:15:22,325
皮特几岁         17岁

2023
01:15:20,397 --> 01:15:22,331
- How old is Pete? - Seventeen.

2024
01:15:23,501 --> 01:15:25,731
告诉我他的事

2025
01:15:23,533 --> 01:15:25,797
<i>Tell me about Pete.</i>

2026
01:15:27,739 --> 01:15:29,866
怎么了？

2027
01:15:27,804 --> 01:15:29,396
What happened?

2028
01:15:29,974 --> 01:15:32,807
出事了吗？

2029
01:15:29,973 --> 01:15:32,339
Is there a problem?

2030
01:15:32,910 --> 01:15:35,105
所以他才叫你来

2031
01:15:32,909 --> 01:15:35,605
<i>Is that why he called you?</i>

2032
01:15:36,714 --> 01:15:38,705
他有个女朋友

2033
01:15:35,679 --> 01:15:38,739
[Sighs] He's got a girlfriend.

2034
01:15:38,816 --> 01:15:41,341
他女朋友有事？      她怀孕了

2035
01:15:38,815 --> 01:15:41,375
<i>- And the problem is with the girlfriend? - She's pregnant.</i>

2036
01:15:41,452 --> 01:15:43,113
他可以想到会变成怎样

2037
01:15:41,451 --> 01:15:44,045
He can see it all coming right down the road. You get married,

2038
01:15:43,221 --> 01:15:44,984
结婚、生子

2039
01:15:44,120 --> 01:15:48,022
have a bunch of kids, wind up in the same job that killed your dad.

2040
01:15:45,089 --> 01:15:47,956
跟他爸做一样的工作

2041
01:15:48,059 --> 01:15:50,425
他怪她？         不…

2042
01:15:48,091 --> 01:15:50,491
<i>- He blames her for this? - Oh, no, no, no.</i>

2043
01:15:50,528 --> 01:15:53,759
他不怪她，他只是…

2044
01:15:50,560 --> 01:15:53,825
He doesn't blame her. No, he just...

2045
01:15:53,865 --> 01:15:56,766
他…他是怎么说的

2046
01:15:53,897 --> 01:15:56,832
He... How did he put it?

2047
01:15:56,868 --> 01:15:59,860
他不懂大家为什么要作茧自缚

2048
01:15:56,900 --> 01:15:59,926
He hates the chains that people shackle themselves with.

2049
01:15:59,971 --> 01:16:03,498
我们K派斯就没这种驴事 好了

2050
01:16:00,003 --> 01:16:02,233
I mean, we don't have all that crap on K-PAX.

2051
01:16:02,305 --> 01:16:06,401
All right, Prot. I want you to listen to me carefully.

2052
01:16:03,875 --> 01:16:06,867
我要你仔细听好

2053
01:16:06,978 --> 01:16:11,005
我要你把时间再往前移

2054
01:16:07,477 --> 01:16:10,037
I want to move forward in time again.

2055
01:16:11,115 --> 01:16:13,049
往前移两个礼拜

2056
01:16:11,114 --> 01:16:13,048
Oh, say, two weeks.

2057
01:16:14,819 --> 01:16:17,549
你…

2058
01:16:14,818 --> 01:16:15,910
You...

2059
01:16:17,655 --> 01:16:21,489
你可以睁开眼睛，到处走走

2060
01:16:17,654 --> 01:16:21,021
If you would like to open your eyes or move around, you may.

2061
01:16:21,592 --> 01:16:24,356
你想不想         我知道可以

2062
01:16:22,092 --> 01:16:24,424
- Would you like to? - I know that.

2063
01:16:29,867 --> 01:16:31,061
波特

2064
01:16:29,866 --> 01:16:31,800
Prot?

2065
01:16:34,839 --> 01:16:37,501
波特…         时间是…

2066
01:16:34,871 --> 01:16:37,533
- Prot, when... - It's, uh,

2067
01:16:37,608 --> 01:16:40,042
1991年

2068
01:16:37,607 --> 01:16:40,098
<i>1991,</i>

2069
01:16:40,144 --> 01:16:43,113
根据你们的地球历

2070
01:16:40,176 --> 01:16:43,145
according to your Earth calendar.

2071
01:16:43,214 --> 01:16:45,375
你朋友皮特叫你

2072
01:16:43,213 --> 01:16:45,408
And your friend Pete called you?

2073
01:16:45,483 --> 01:16:47,348
不是因为发生什么事

2074
01:16:45,482 --> 01:16:47,416
Not for anything in particular.

2075
01:16:47,452 --> 01:16:51,616
只是有时候，他想聊一聊

2076
01:16:47,484 --> 01:16:51,682
He just... sometimes wants to talk things over...

2077
01:16:53,291 --> 01:16:56,488
找人谈谈心事

2078
01:16:53,289 --> 01:16:56,554
with someone every now and then.

2079
01:16:56,861 --> 01:16:58,488
告诉我他做什么

2080
01:16:56,626 --> 01:16:58,560
Tell me about Pete now.

2081
01:16:58,596 --> 01:17:01,997
他是个击昏者         击昏者？

2082
01:16:58,628 --> 01:17:02,064
- He's a knocker. - A "knocker"?

2083
01:17:02,100 --> 01:17:05,194
就是负责把牛击昏

2084
01:17:02,132 --> 01:17:05,260
A knocker is the guy that knocks the cow inside of the head...

2085
01:17:05,303 --> 01:17:08,500
让它乖乖的任人宰割

2086
01:17:05,335 --> 01:17:08,566
<i>so it won't struggle while they slit its throat.</i>

2087
01:17:09,207 --> 01:17:13,109
我知道，很野蛮，对不对

2088
01:17:08,638 --> 01:17:12,130
I know. It's barbaric, isn't it?

2089
01:17:13,478 --> 01:17:15,412
他还住在同一个地方

2090
01:17:13,209 --> 01:17:15,439
Does he still live in the same town?

2091
01:17:16,013 --> 01:17:20,916
他住在镇外，有间小房子 整理得不错

2092
01:17:15,512 --> 01:17:18,447
Oh, just outside of town.

2093
01:17:18,515 --> 01:17:21,006
He's got a little place, but he's fixed it up nice.

2094
01:17:21,018 --> 01:17:26,149
有树、有几亩地…

2095
01:17:21,084 --> 01:17:25,885
It's got some... trees and a couple of acres...

2096
01:17:30,495 --> 01:17:32,395
还有一条河

2097
01:17:30,527 --> 01:17:32,461
and a river.

2098
01:17:37,168 --> 01:17:40,228
没有那条河，就很像K派斯

2099
01:17:37,200 --> 01:17:40,294
It reminds me of K-PAX, except for the river.

2100
01:17:44,642 --> 01:17:48,442
告诉我，他有没有娶他女朋友

2101
01:17:44,274 --> 01:17:48,506
Tell me, did he ever marry that pregnant girl?

2102
01:17:50,782 --> 01:17:52,716
哇，你记性真好

2103
01:17:50,780 --> 01:17:52,748
Wow, what a memory.

2104
01:17:52,817 --> 01:17:54,910
他们结婚了，都生了一个小孩

2105
01:17:52,816 --> 01:17:57,378
Yeah, they got married, but she's no longer pregnant. Why, that was six years ago.

2106
01:17:55,019 --> 01:17:57,283
那是六年前的事

2107
01:17:58,456 --> 01:18:00,754
我忘了她叫什么名字

2108
01:17:58,454 --> 01:18:00,820
I've forgotten her name.

2109
01:18:00,858 --> 01:18:02,758
莎…

2110
01:18:00,890 --> 01:18:02,824
S...

2111
01:18:05,763 --> 01:18:07,230
我没跟你说过她的名字

2112
01:18:05,361 --> 01:18:07,295
I didn't tell you her name.

2113
01:18:07,732 --> 01:18:09,324
你可以告诉我吗？

2114
01:18:07,363 --> 01:18:09,331
Can you tell me now?

2115
01:18:25,783 --> 01:18:27,910
莎拉

2116
01:18:25,782 --> 01:18:27,977
Sara.

2117
01:18:35,693 --> 01:18:38,594
他们生了个男孩还是女孩

2118
01:18:35,692 --> 01:18:38,627
<i>Did they have a son or a daughter?</i>

2119
01:18:43,601 --> 01:18:45,535
丽贝卡

2120
01:18:43,600 --> 01:18:45,534
Rebecca.

2121
01:18:51,876 --> 01:18:53,309
丽贝卡

2122
01:18:51,407 --> 01:18:53,341
Rebecca.

2123
01:18:58,683 --> 01:19:01,516
下个礼拜是她生日

2124
01:18:58,681 --> 01:19:01,548
It's her birthday next week.

2125
01:19:22,607 --> 01:19:25,542
查克，怎么回事 豪伊想杀恩尼

2126
01:19:22,605 --> 01:19:25,574
<i>- Chak, what's happened? - Howie tried to kill Ernie.</i>

2127
01:19:25,643 --> 01:19:28,134
什么？         他没事

2128
01:19:25,642 --> 01:19:27,803
- What? - He's fine.

2129
01:19:29,981 --> 01:19:31,005
恩尼

2130
01:19:29,946 --> 01:19:33,814
- Ernie? - I feel wonderful, Dr. Powell.

2131
01:19:32,350 --> 01:19:34,113
鲍威尔医生，我觉得很好

2132
01:19:34,218 --> 01:19:35,981
真的很好 发生什么事？

2133
01:19:33,883 --> 01:19:35,976
- For heaven's sake. What happened? - Absolutely wonderful.

2134
01:19:37,188 --> 01:19:41,648
我的好朋友豪伊，差点勒死我

2135
01:19:37,453 --> 01:19:41,719
My good friend Howie, he just about strangled me to death.

2136
01:19:41,759 --> 01:19:43,192
什么？

