01:28:57,379 --> 01:29:00,371
That's pretty damn close to Santa Rosa.

2382
01:29:00,451 --> 01:29:02,885
那一区最大的地方报是什么报

2383
01:29:00,449 --> 01:29:02,940
What's the biggest local newspaper for that region?

2384
01:29:04,388 --> 01:29:07,755
瓜县观察报，报导当地的新闻

2385
01:29:04,453 --> 01:29:07,820
<i>Guadalupe County Observer, covering Guadalupe County.</i>

2386
01:29:07,858 --> 01:29:09,792
好，去他们的网站

2387
01:29:07,890 --> 01:29:09,824
All right. Bring that up.

2388
01:29:10,727 --> 01:29:14,823
去看1996年7月27日

2389
01:29:10,893 --> 01:29:14,852
<i>Go to July 27, 1996.</i>

2390
01:29:16,533 --> 01:29:19,468
跳蚤市场…牲口买卖…

2391
01:29:16,532 --> 01:29:19,501
<i>"Swap meet, livestock sale. '"</i>

2392
01:29:19,570 --> 01:29:21,470
去看28日

2393
01:29:19,568 --> 01:29:21,536
Wait. Go to the 28th.

2394
01:29:21,604 --> 01:29:23,196
<i>Okay.</i>

2395
01:29:24,408 --> 01:29:28,777
找到了，罗伯波特，溺毙

2396
01:29:23,272 --> 01:29:25,638
[Gasps] There it is!

2397
01:29:25,708 --> 01:29:28,802
"Robert Porter. Drowned!"

2398
01:29:29,813 --> 01:29:32,611
他的名字…

2399
01:29:29,879 --> 01:29:31,938
His name...

2400
01:29:32,716 --> 01:29:34,741
就叫罗伯波特

2401
01:29:32,515 --> 01:29:34,506
is Robert Porter.

2402
01:29:52,469 --> 01:29:56,303
“戈福      5英里” “圣罗莎23英里”

2403
01:30:02,846 --> 01:30:06,145
“瓜县警局”

2404
01:30:07,683 --> 01:30:09,617
<i>[Bell Dings]</i>

2405
01:30:09,653 --> 01:30:11,951
“7月25日”

2406
01:30:12,121 --> 01:30:14,646
<i>[Footsteps]</i>

2407
01:30:16,426 --> 01:30:19,259
罗伯波特，找到了

2408
01:30:16,225 --> 01:30:19,319
<i>Robert Porter. Ah, here it is.</i>

2409
01:30:20,397 --> 01:30:21,955
我记得这件案子

2410
01:30:20,396 --> 01:30:22,330
Yeah, I do remember this case.

2411
01:30:22,065 --> 01:30:24,966
当年曾经轰动一时

2412
01:30:22,398 --> 01:30:25,094
<i>It was about the biggest thing ever happened around these parts.</i>

2413
01:30:26,637 --> 01:30:27,569
沉默寡言

2414
01:30:26,569 --> 01:30:29,766
He was a quiet type.

2415
01:30:29,806 --> 01:30:33,298
我印象中，他是个聪明的家伙

2416
01:30:29,838 --> 01:30:33,399
As I recall, he was a real smart fella. Kind of brainy.

2417
01:30:33,944 --> 01:30:36,037
而且力气非常大

2418
01:30:33,475 --> 01:30:36,103
Strong as a horse, though, and worked as a knocker.

2419
01:30:36,146 --> 01:30:40,014
住在镇外廿英里的地方 夫妻两生了一个女儿

2420
01:30:36,178 --> 01:30:40,114
Lived about 20 miles outside of town with his-his wife and child.

2421
01:30:42,185 --> 01:30:46,121
莎拉，他太太叫莎拉

2422
01:30:42,017 --> 01:30:43,177
Sarah.

2423
01:30:44,253 --> 01:30:46,187
His wife's name was Sarah.

2424
01:30:46,790 --> 01:30:48,621
没错

2425
01:30:46,255 --> 01:30:48,655
That's right.

2426
01:30:48,725 --> 01:30:50,989
一件悲剧

2427
01:30:48,724 --> 01:30:51,022
Damn shame what happened.

2428
01:30:53,263 --> 01:30:56,164
想不想去看看？         好

2429
01:30:52,494 --> 01:30:54,428
You got time to take a ride?

2430
01:30:54,496 --> 01:30:55,622
Yeah.

2431
01:31:22,326 --> 01:31:25,056
房子一直空着

2432
01:31:22,324 --> 01:31:24,417
Well, it's been empty.

2433
01:31:25,696 --> 01:31:30,292
事发之后就没人来过

2434
01:31:25,728 --> 01:31:27,889
Yeah, nobody comes around here much anymore...

2435
01:31:27,963 --> 01:31:30,329
since all that happened.

2436
01:31:32,102 --> 01:31:35,538
也没有亲属继承

2437
01:31:32,101 --> 01:31:35,559
Ain't no livin' next of kin to give the place to anyway.

2438
01:31:45,649 --> 01:31:48,015
城里派了警探

2439
01:31:45,648 --> 01:31:48,082
I had detectives come down from Albuquerque...

2440
01:31:48,952 --> 01:31:50,783
把案发的经过拼凑出来

2441
01:31:48,150 --> 01:31:50,846
to try and piece this one together.

2442
01:31:56,426 --> 01:31:58,394
官方的说法是…

2443
01:31:56,659 --> 01:31:59,526
<i>Well, accordin'to the official story,</i>

2444
01:31:59,563 --> 01:32:04,193
波特出去干活的时候 有一个叫戴洛的流浪汉

2445
01:31:59,595 --> 01:32:02,428
Porter, he was at work when this, uh, this drifter,

2446
01:32:02,498 --> 01:32:06,366
Darryl Walker, come by the house.

2447
01:32:04,635 --> 01:32:06,262
跑来家里

2448
01:32:06,370 --> 01:32:10,329
他坐过两次牢，来意不善

2449
01:32:06,435 --> 01:32:09,893
Two-time parolee lookin' for trouble. You know what I'm sayin'?

2450
01:32:10,841 --> 01:32:12,331
起先打算抢劫

2451
01:32:10,472 --> 01:32:12,406
Started out as a robbery.

2452
01:32:12,843 --> 01:32:16,335
他老婆跟女儿在后面

2453
01:32:12,474 --> 01:32:14,374
<i>The wife and the daughter were out back.</i>

2454
01:32:17,414 --> 01:32:18,938
莎拉？

2455
01:32:17,279 --> 01:32:18,371
Sarah?

2456
01:32:20,050 --> 01:32:21,312
莎拉？

2457
01:32:19,281 --> 01:32:20,578
<i>[Voice Echoes] Sarah?</i>

2458
01:32:21,418 --> 01:32:24,683
根据现场收集到的资料

2459
01:32:22,317 --> 01:32:24,751
From what we can gather from forensics and all,

2460
01:32:24,788 --> 01:32:28,588
那家伙逼她们母女进屋

2461
01:32:24,820 --> 01:32:28,654
this Walker, he, uh... he forced the two women into the house.

2462
01:32:39,636 --> 01:32:44,505
先强奸了母亲，然后杀了她们

2463
01:32:38,967 --> 01:32:41,697
Raped the wife,

2464
01:32:41,770 --> 01:32:44,568
<i>killed 'em both.</i>

2465
01:32:49,713 --> 01:32:52,580
波特一定是回家撞到了他

2466
01:32:49,712 --> 01:32:52,647
Porter, he must've come home and found Walker still here.

2467
01:33:06,363 --> 01:33:08,422
天哪

2468
01:33:06,428 --> 01:33:07,520
God.

2469
01:33:08,532 --> 01:33:11,467
一把就扭断了他的脖子

2470
01:33:08,597 --> 01:33:11,566
Snapped a grown man's neck like it was a twig.

2471
01:33:11,633 --> 01:33:13,999
<i>[Shouts]</i>

2472
01:33:26,648 --> 01:33:28,980
[Grunts]

2473
01:33:31,653 --> 01:33:35,885
<i>?? [Woman Vocalizing]</i>

2474
01:34:09,292 --> 01:34:11,920
换了我也会那么做

2475
01:34:09,324 --> 01:34:11,986
Can't say I wouldn't have done the same myself.

2476
01:34:44,026 --> 01:34:47,553
<i>?? [Vocalizing Continues]</i>

2477
01:35:35,111 --> 01:35:37,511
河在那个方向

2478
01:35:34,543 --> 01:35:37,034
Uh, the river's this way.

2479
01:36:10,680 --> 01:36:13,240
他们在那里发现他的衣服

2480
01:36:10,712 --> 01:36:12,805
They found the clothes there.

2481
01:36:15,218 --> 01:36:18,745
他大概是从那里跳进去

2482
01:36:15,250 --> 01:36:17,810
That's probably where he jumped in.

2483
01:36:18,855 --> 01:36:22,484
这条河的河水非常湍急

2484
01:36:18,720 --> 01:36:20,688
<i>And this river can be pretty treacherous.</i>

2485
01:36:20,722 --> 01:36:22,587
<i>Even in July it's got a hell of a current.</i>

2486
01:36:23,026 --> 01:36:26,723
到现在我都觉得不应该

2487
01:36:22,658 --> 01:36:26,788
Still, I suppose it might have been a mistake, officially,

2488
01:36:27,430 --> 01:36:31,389
没找到尸体就宣布他溺毙

2489
01:36:26,862 --> 01:36:30,798
to declare it a drowning when the body was never found.

2490
01:36:31,501 --> 01:36:36,063
医生，假如那个人真的是波特

2491
01:36:30,866 --> 01:36:32,333
Doc,

2492
01:36:32,901 --> 01:36:36,132
<i>if that boy you got back there in New York is really Robert Porter,</i>

2493
01:36:36,907 --> 01:36:41,139
我也宁愿不知道 你明白我的意思吧

2494
01:36:36,204 --> 01:36:38,934
<i>I'd just as soon not know about it.</i>

2495
01:36:39,007 --> 01:36:41,202
<i>Know what I mean?</i>

2496
01:37:50,112 --> 01:37:51,204
Mark.

2497
01:37:54,884 --> 01:37:56,408
对不起，对不起

2498
01:37:54,416 --> 01:37:56,509
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

2499
01:37:56,519 --> 01:37:59,511
以后别这样         再也不会了

2500
01:37:56,585 --> 01:37:59,076
- Never do that again. - I won't.

2501
01:37:59,622 --> 01:38:01,715
怎么回事？

2502
01:37:59,654 --> 01:38:01,019
What happened?

2503
01:38:02,759 --> 01:38:05,125
我找到要找的资料了

2504
01:38:01,857 --> 01:38:04,883
I found what I was looking for.

2505
01:38:06,162 --> 01:38:08,494
你确定？         确定

2506
01:38:06,128 --> 01:38:07,595
- You sure? - Yeah.

2507
01:38:10,000 --> 01:38:12,798
我宁愿我没找到

2508
01:38:10,032 --> 01:38:12,023
Wish I hadn't.

2509
01:38:20,609 --> 01:38:24,306
<i>? And I think it's gonna be a long, long time?</i>

2510
01:38:24,379 --> 01:38:27,837
<i>- ? Till touch down brings me round again to find? - [Tooting]</i>

2511
01:38:27,916 --> 01:38:30,908
<i>? I'm not the man they think I am at home?</i>

2512
01:38:30,986 --> 01:38:33,716
<i>? Oh, no, no, no?</i>

2513
01:38:33,789 --> 01:38:37,748
<i>- ? I'm a rocket man? - [Tooting]</i>

2514
01:38:37,794 --> 01:38:40,354
豪伊，把我的放在上面

2515
01:38:37,826 --> 01:38:40,488
If you wouldn't mind putting mine on top.

2516
01:38:40,562 --> 01:38:43,224
<i>? Burnin'out his fuse up here alone?</i>

2517
01:38:43,298 --> 01:38:45,766
<i>[Tooting]</i>

2518
01:38:48,737 --> 01:38:52,002
<i>? And I think it's gonna be a long, long time??</i>

2519
01:39:00,350 --> 01:39:01,544
波特

2520
01:39:00,382 --> 01:39:01,406
Prot.

2521
01:39:03,286 --> 01:39:05,254
坐

2522
01:39:03,351 --> 01:39:04,784
Have a seat.

2523
01:39:07,524 --> 01:39:10,618
都准备好了？随时可以走

2524
01:39:07,556 --> 01:39:10,719
You all packed? Ready to go?

2525
01:39:10,727 --> 01:39:14,219
差不多，我光身体走

2526
01:39:10,792 --> 01:39:13,454
Quite ready. I travel light.

2527
01:39:14,330 --> 01:39:16,992
开玩笑的

2528
01:39:14,362 --> 01:39:17,058
- That's a joke, Mark. - [Chuckles]

2529
01:39:17,100 --> 01:39:20,934
你们人类，真没幽默感

2530
01:39:17,132 --> 01:39:20,499
You humans. There's just no sense of humor.

2531
01:39:21,037 --> 01:39:26,805
我怀疑弗洛伊德会不会这样 有人要离开

2532
01:39:21,069 --> 01:39:24,869
I doubt, uh, Freud ever tried this,

2533
01:39:24,940 --> 01:39:26,874
but before someone goes away,

2534
01:39:26,910 --> 01:39:29,936
通常我们会喝酒，替他饯行

2535
01:39:26,942 --> 01:39:30,002
we usually like to send them off with a little toast.

2536
01:39:30,046 --> 01:39:34,346
威士忌可以吧？还是要水果酒

2537
01:39:30,078 --> 01:39:34,412
Scotch okay, or would you prefer something more fruity?

2538
01:39:35,685 --> 01:39:38,017
威士忌就可以

2539
01:39:35,717 --> 01:39:38,117
I will try the scotch.

2540
01:39:44,527 --> 01:39:46,392
那…

2541
01:39:44,559 --> 01:39:46,493
Well,

2542
01:39:46,496 --> 01:39:48,555
祝你

2543
01:39:46,561 --> 01:39:48,586
here's to a...

2544
01:39:48,665 --> 01:39:51,293
一路顺风

2545
01:39:48,663 --> 01:39:50,893
safe journey.

2546
01:40:12,889 --> 01:40:14,914
老实说…

2547
01:40:12,921 --> 01:40:14,980
Tell you the truth,

2548
01:40:16,292 --> 01:40:19,853
K派斯听起来是个不错的地方

2549
01:40:16,358 --> 01:40:19,156
K-PAX sounds like a beautiful place.

2550
01:40:20,730 --> 01:40:24,325
我想去见识见识 你想有没有机会？

2551
01:40:20,729 --> 01:40:24,392
I'd like to see it sometime. Think there's a chance of that?

2552
01:40:25,435 --> 01:40:27,733
我认为你应该多看看你的世界

2553
01:40:25,567 --> 01:40:27,831
I think you should see more of your world.

2554
01:40:28,738 --> 01:40:31,502
尤其是多见见你的家人

2555
01:40:27,903 --> 01:40:31,566
As a matter of fact, I think you should see more of your own family.

2556
01:40:32,775 --> 01:40:35,141
请你儿子来过圣诞节

2557
01:40:32,741 --> 01:40:35,209
Invite your son for Christmas.

2558
01:40:38,281 --> 01:40:41,114
我应该会

2559
01:40:38,313 --> 01:40:41,180
I may just do that, Prot.

2560
01:40:43,086 --> 01:40:45,748
你知道我这一趟有什么感触

2561
01:40:43,084 --> 01:40:45,814
You know what I've learned about your planet?

2562
01:40:45,855 --> 01:40:49,222
地球的生物多到 能住满五十个星球

2563
01:40:45,887 --> 01:40:49,323
There's enough life on Earth to fill 50 planets...

2564
01:40:49,325 --> 01:40:52,385
植物、动物、人 细菌、病毒…

2565
01:40:49,391 --> 01:40:52,451
plants, animals, people, fungi, viruses...

2566
01:40:52,495 --> 01:40:55,225
你推我挤的，设法生存

2567
01:40:52,527 --> 01:40:55,291
all jostling to find their place,

2568
01:40:55,331 --> 01:40:58,198
撞来撞去，互相依赖

2569
01:40:55,363 --> 01:40:58,298
bouncing off each other, feeding off each other,

2570
01:41:00,236 --> 01:41:01,225
建立关系

2571
01:41:00,035 --> 01:41:01,297
connected.

2572
01:41:03,072 --> 01:41:07,008
在K派斯没有这种关系？

2573
01:41:03,138 --> 01:41:07,097
You don't have that kind of connection on K-PAX?

2574
01:41:08,011 --> 01:41:09,706
无欲无求

2575
01:41:07,676 --> 01:41:09,769
Nobody wants, nobody needs.

2576
01:41:09,812 --> 01:41:12,144
就算我离开K派斯 也不会有人怀念我

2577
01:41:09,844 --> 01:41:12,210
On K-PAX, when I'm gone, nobody misses me.

2578
01:41:12,248 --> 01:41:14,944
因为没有理由

2579
01:41:12,280 --> 01:41:14,510
There would be no reason to.

2580
01:41:15,051 --> 01:41:17,679
可是我觉得离开这里

2581
01:41:15,083 --> 01:41:17,779
And yet I sense that when I leave here,

2582
01:41:21,257 --> 01:41:22,724
我会被人怀念

2583
01:41:20,855 --> 01:41:22,789
I will be missed.

2584
01:41:25,328 --> 01:41:26,260
对

2585
01:41:25,227 --> 01:41:26,319
Yes.

2586
01:41:28,031 --> 01:41:30,056
奇怪的感觉

2587
01:41:28,096 --> 01:41:30,121
Strange feeling.

2588
01:41:30,166 --> 01:41:32,634
你不一定要走

2589
01:41:30,198 --> 01:41:32,723
You don't have to leave, Prot.

2590
01:41:33,403 --> 01:41:36,702
留下来，我会想办法帮你

2591
01:41:32,801 --> 01:41:36,737
I'm sure there must be some way that I can help you...

2592
01:41:36,806 --> 01:41:40,867
变成我们的一份子

2593
01:41:36,805 --> 01:41:40,901
to stay as one of us.

2594
01:41:47,951 --> 01:41:51,182
我会想念你的，鲍威尔医生

2595
01:41:47,782 --> 01:41:51,274
I will miss you, Dr. Powell.

2596
01:41:55,291 --> 01:41:57,122
“瓜县高中”

2597
01:42:02,097 --> 01:42:03,189
Oh.

2598
01:42:04,100 --> 01:42:06,500
我得把报告写完，可是…

2599
01:42:04,099 --> 01:42:06,533
And I have to finish my report, but...

2600
01:42:09,138 --> 01:42:12,733
铅笔好像被我弄丢了

2601
01:42:09,137 --> 01:42:12,106
I seem to have misplaced my pencil.

2602
01:42:25,655 --> 01:42:27,122
用我的

2603
01:42:25,253 --> 01:42:27,187
Take mine.

2604
01:42:35,298 --> 01:42:38,426
更方便的书写工具

2605
01:42:35,297 --> 01:42:38,460
A much more efficient writing tool.

2606
01:42:44,240 --> 01:42:45,798
再会了，我的朋友

2607
01:42:43,938 --> 01:42:45,872
Adios, my friend.

2608
01:42:49,077 --> 01:42:50,135
Prot?

2609
01:42:51,514 --> 01:42:53,948
我给你看一样东西

2610
01:42:51,546 --> 01:42:53,980
I wanna show you something.

2611
01:43:04,060 --> 01:43:05,584
那是罗伯波特

2612
01:43:03,892 --> 01:43:05,553
That is Robert Porter.

2613
01:43:05,662 --> 01:43:08,529
波特，那是你

2614
01:43:05,593 --> 01:43:08,289
Prot, that's you.

2615
01:43:08,598 --> 01:43:11,192
你就是罗伯波特

2616
01:43:08,697 --> 01:43:11,097
You and Robert Porter are the same person.

2617
01:43:12,135 --> 01:43:15,195
太可笑了，我根本不是人类

2618
01:43:12,300 --> 01:43:15,235
That's patently absurd. I'm not even human.

2619
01:43:15,305 --> 01:43:18,763
你就不能承认有那个可能

2620
01:43:15,270 --> 01:43:18,171
Can't you at least admit the possibility?

2621
01:43:19,309 --> 01:43:22,745
要我承认我有可能是罗伯波特

2622
01:43:18,907 --> 01:43:22,240
I will admit the possibility that I am Robert Porter...

2623
01:43:23,246 --> 01:43:26,215
